            <scopecontent>
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                                 <p>This collection contains photocopies of documents relating to the trials of the murderers of Joseph and Hyrum Smith, the Mormon leaders who were killed by a mob in Carthage, Ill., in 1844. These items include a published transcript of the trial of Joseph Smith&#039;s murderers; two excerpts taken from the official Circuit Court Journal record of that trial; and a list of witnesses subpoenaed for the trial of Hyrum Smith&#039;s murderers. The collection also contains a copy of a Guardian Bond stating that Joseph Smith, Hyrum Smith and William Law share responsibilities for the Lawrence children.</p>
                                 <p>Eugene Johnson donated the photocopies to the Illinois Historical Survey in 1973.</p>
                        </scopecontent>
            


